  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">KHI Ghana Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">(i)	Develop infrastructure:  The project will add to the country&apos;s critical lack of business infrastructure. 
(ii)	Job creation:  The hotel and associated development will create new direct and indirect employment.  
(iii)	Benefits to local suppliers:  The hotel is expected to source almost all of their food and non-food purchases locally, thereby providing increased business opportunities to a wide range of local suppliers and sub-contractors, most of whom are SMEs.  Going forward, KHI Ghana&apos;s operations are expected to offer a significant revenue source to these SMEs, thereby enhancing their competitiveness and growth.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Greenfield project consist of developing: (i) a 259-key 5-star hotel to be managed by M&#xF6;venpick; (ii) 9,000m2 of Class A office space (with gross lettable area 5,500m2); and (iii) 1,260m2 of retail space (with gross lettable area 900m2) in Accra, the capital of Ghana (the Project).</narrative>
  </description>
